<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <!-- Get bootstrap library for styling -->
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/bootstrap.min.css" />
    <title>Youngest olympian</title>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container p-3">
        <nav aria-label="breadcrumb">
            <ol class="breadcrumb">
                <li class="breadcrumb-item"><a href="/">Home</a></li>
                <li class="breadcrumb-item active" aria-current="page">Youngest Olympian</li>
            </ol>
        </nav>
        <h1>Youngest Olympian across Games from 2010 - 2016</h1>
        The table below shows the youngest Olympian across the Games.
        When delving into their sport (click the rightmost column), it
        is evident that all three athletes are swimmers. This is interesting as
        it shows that swimmers typically start competing when they are young.
        <table class = "table">
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Name</th>
                    <th>Sex</th>
                    <th>Age</th>
                    <th>Height</th>
                    <th>Country</th>
                    <th>Link to games</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <% data.forEach((item) => { %>
                <tr>
                    <td><%= item.name%> </td>
                    <td><%= item.sex%> </td>
                    <td><%= item.age %></td>
                    <td><%= item.height %></td>
                    <td><%= item.team %></td>
                    <td>
                        <form action="/athlete" method = "GET" class = "my-1">
                            <input type="hidden" name="athlete_id" value = <%=item.athlete_id%> >
                            <button class="btn btn-outline-dark" type="submit">Athlete details</button>
                        </form>
                    </td>
                </tr>
            <% }); %>
        </table>
        </div>
</body>
</html>